---

### Module 1 — Azure Foundations

#### 📖 Session overview
This session introduces the core building blocks of Azure — the platform that holds the DSR landing zone. It covers how Microsoft organises resources in Azure (tenants, subscriptions, resource groups), how regions and redundancy zones work, and how DIA's naming and tagging conventions map onto these concepts. By the end of the session you'll be able to navigate the Azure portal confidently and understand why our resources are named the way they are.

#### 🎯 What you'll learn
- The difference between a tenant, subscription, resource group, and resource
- How Azure regions and Availability Zones provide redundancy (and why we picked NZ North + ZRS)
- How Azure RBAC works — the difference between Owner, Contributor, and Reader
- How DIA's naming standard (`rg-dia-anl-nzn-{net,stor,app,svc,mgt}-<env>`) and tagging standard (`app_name=anl`, `org_name=dia`) work
- How to deploy your first resource into your own training subscription

#### 📚 Before this session — Microsoft Learn pre-work
- *Describe core Azure concepts* (~30 min) — overview of cloud computing
- *Describe Azure architecture and services* (~45 min) — regions, subscriptions, resource groups
- *Describe Azure identity, access, and security* (~30 min) — RBAC, Entra ID basics

*(The standard Microsoft Learn module names will be linked in the GitHub repo so each pre-work item opens directly to the right page.)*

#### ⏱️ EDE accounting
- Trainee self-paced: 90 min
- Instructor-led delivery: 1.5h
- Prep work (MS Learn): ~1.5h
- Q&A: 30 min
- **Total EDE per trainee: ~5h**

#### 💰 Cost
- < NZD $0.50 (a single Standard storage account left running for the lab; torn down at end)

#### 🔤 Acronyms used
- **RBAC** = Role-Based Access Control
- **ARM** = Azure Resource Manager (the API that deploys everything in Azure)
- **ZRS** = Zone-Redundant Storage (data replicated across 3 Availability Zones in the region)

#### ⌨️ Activities (summary)
1. Sign in to your training subscription via `portal.azure.com`
2. Create a resource group following DIA's naming standard
3. Apply DIA's tagging standard
4. Deploy a Standard storage account (smallest SKU)
5. Inspect the resource in the portal — JSON view, activity log, IAM
6. Tear down

#### ✅ Success checklist
- [ ] You can sign in to your training subscription
- [ ] You've created and tagged a resource group
- [ ] You've deployed and torn down a storage account
- [ ] You can explain the difference between a subscription and a resource group

